sentences: After working for a time in music production, in 2001 he released his debut solo album through Universal Records.
He afterwards released several albums with The Ike Reilly Assassination, including the well-received Sparkle in the Finish in 2004, through Rock Ridge Music.
He released his eighth album of solo material, Crooked Love, in May 2018.
In 1989, though still pursuing music, Reilly took a job at the Park Hyatt Chicago, where he remained until the hotel was torn down.
He pursued alternate paths after leaving his work at the Hyatt, becoming a freelance production assistant and, in 1997, opened the Diamond City recording studio with engineer Blaise Barton.
After taking a musical hiatus, Reilly continued to write songs and started recording in 1998 with engineer Ed Tinley, who had worked with Liz Phair, Smashing Pumpkins, and R. Kelly.
A month later Reilly signed a recording contract with Universal Republic Records, where he released his critically acclaimed debut album Salesmen And Racists in 2001.
Reilly parted ways with Universal in 2003, and since been releasing music on Rock Ridge Music.
The group released their first album as a group, Sparkle in the Finish, in 2004.

On May 18, Reilly released "Crooked Love."
He decided to retire from music in the early 1990s.
He started his music career with various rock bands near his hometown of Libertyville, Illinois, playing guitar for groups such as The Drovers in the late 1980s.

According to Mario Mesquita Borges of Allmusic, "Reilly has followed a trail separate from most of today's singer/songwriters -- unlike other such artists, Reilly prefers the harshness of intrepid rocking riffs, sustained by ingenious melodies and exalting words."
Reilly learned to play guitar while working at Ascension Catholic Cemetery, a job he held every summer through high school and college.
